{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_0129Ha95e2Sc8Z9BLd8M5xtn","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting! The `users` and `users_roles` files inside the pod are empty. This might be because of the `subPath` mount in the StatefulSet. When Kubernetes volumes are mounted with `subPath`, the volume is NOT updated automatically when the underlying Secret changes. This is a known Kubernetes limitation.\n\nLooking at the StatefulSet:\n```yaml\nvolumeMounts:\n  - name: file-realm\n    mountPath: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/users\n    subPath: users\n    readOnly: true\n  - name: file-realm\n    mountPath: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/users_roles\n    subPath: users_roles\n    readOnly: true\n  - name: file-realm\n    mountPath: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/roles.yml\n    subPath: roles.yml\n    readOnly: true\n```\n\nThe `subPath` is the culprit. When you use `subPath`, Kubernetes does NOT update the file when the secret is updated (unlike regular volume mounts without subPath). So even though the secret is updated, the file in the pod won't change without a pod restart.\n\nBut wait, the files are showing as empty (`---`). Let me re-examine what the actual file contents are.\n\nLooking at the precondition log more carefully, the secrets were created after the cluster was already running with those four pods, which means the file realm files would have been mounted when the pods initially started. Since the pods were already running with subPath mounts pointing to those secrets, I need to check what's actually in the users file inside the pod right now.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":321,"cache_read_input_tokens":43417,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":321},"output_tokens":34,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnosti