{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01QLAXLmh4cbPeAjV3vF79Jn","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `users` and `users_roles` files inside the pod are empty and dated Nov 11 2023 (the image build date). Looking at the directory listing, I see `http-certs` directory is NOT listed but there is a `tls` directory.\n\nThis is interesting! The files `users` and `users_roles` in the pod are NOT the mounted files from the secret - they seem to be the original files from the Docker image. \n\nLet me look more carefully. The StatefulSet uses `subPath` mounts:\nThe mount is configured to place the secret's `users` file at `/usr/share/elasticsearch/config/users` with read-only access, but the file listing shows 0 bytes owned by root from the image build date—which means the secret mount isn't actually overriding the original image file. With `subPath` binding, this shouldn't happen unless the secret itself is empty or the mount isn't being applied correctly.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1171,"cache_read_input_tokens":43738,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1171},"output_tokens":35,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7e179615-5b60-4d30-9419-ea104fd0d74c","uuid":"e0a0e599-22f3-4e1b-841b-36f0275e0d2a","request_id":"req_011CcP4ZmUxmVxb1cgsHKYfP"}
